<h2>Start</h2>
All new students complete the following 4 modules. These are useful courses that all students will use in other classes (English, Math, Sciences and Social Studies) and many carreers.
<ul>
	<li>
		<h2><img src="COM1005 Google Classroom 1000-250.png" width="200px" alt=""/> COM1005: VISUAL COMPOSITION or DES1020: THE DESIGN PROCESS  </h2>
			<button class="collapsible">Expand - Program of Studies</button>
			<div class="content">
			  <p>Students learn to employ fundamental elements and principles of design for various media and gain a strong foundational multidisciplinary experience in preparation for other Communication Technology courses. Students develop an understanding of design problems through research and select, generate and evaluate possible solutions. <em>Prerequisite: None </em> </p>
			</div>
	</li>
	<li>
		<h2><img src="INF1030 Google Classroom 1000-250.png" width="200px"  alt=""/> INF1030: Word Processing 1 </h2>
			<button class="collapsible">Expand - Program of Studies</button>
			<div class="content">
			  <p>Students are introduced to the proper use of word processing software, including document creation, editing and printing of properly formatted documents. <em>Prerequisite: None </em> </p>
			</div>
	</li>
	<li>
		<h2><img src="INF1060 Google Classroom 1000-250.png" width="200px"  alt=""/> INF1060: Spreadsheet 1 </h2>
		<button class="collapsible">Expand - Program of Studies</button>
		<div class="content">
		  <p>Students develop skills in the proper use of spreadsheet software through general data manipulation and personal recordkeeping. <em>Prerequisite: None </em> </p>
		</div>
	</li>
	<li>
		<h2><img src="INF2020 Google Classroom 1000-250.png" width="200px" alt=""/> INF2020: Keyboarding </h2>	
		<button class="collapsible">Expand - Program of Studies</button>
		<div class="content">
		  <p>Students enhance their occupational level keyboarding competence of all keystroke functions, using unedited, edited and straight copy material. <em>Prerequisite: None	</em> </p>
		</div>
	</li>
</ul>
<hr>
<h2>Building and Designing Web Pages </h2>
<ul>
	<li>
		<h2><img src="COM1055 Google Classroom 1000-250.png" width="200px"  alt=""/> COM1055 Web Design 1 </h2>
		<button class="collapsible">Expand - Program of Studies</button>
		<div class="content">
			<p>Students research the characteristics of effective Web page(s) and learn World Wide Web Consortium (W3C) conventions and accessibility concerns to construct a simple Web page. <em>Prerequisite: COM1005: Visual Composition </em> </p>
		</div>
	</li>
	<li>
		<h2><img src="COM2055 Google Classroom 1000-250.png" width="200px"  alt=""/> COM2055 Web Design 2 </h2>
		<button class="collapsible">Expand - Program of Studies</button>
		<div class="content">
			<p>Students learn intermediate coding and software applications to produce a Web site. <em>Prerequisite: COM1055: Web Design 1 </em> </p>
		</div>
	</li>
	<li>
		<h2><img src="COM3075 Google Classroom 1000-250.png" width="200px"  alt=""/> COM3075 CSS Cascading Style Sheet </h2>
		<button class="collapsible">Expand - Program of Studies</button>
		<div class="content">
			<p>Students develop accessible and standards-compliant Web pages using current techniques for advanced cascading style sheets (CSS). <em>Prerequisite: COM2055: Web Design 2 </em> </p>
		</div>
	</li>
</ul>
<hr>
<h2>Computer Programming </h2>
<ul>
	<li>
		<h2><img src="CSE1010 Google Classroom 1000-250.png" width="200px"  alt=""/> CSE1010 Computer Science 1 (Scratch) </h2>
		<button class="collapsible">Expand - Program of Studies</button>
		<div class="content">
			<p>Students explore hardware, software and processes. This includes an introduction to the algorithm as a problem-solving tool, to programming languages in general and to the role of programming as a tool for implementing algorithms. <em>Prerequisite: None  </em> </p>
		</div>
	</li>
	<li>
		<h2><img src="CSE1110 Google Classroom 1000-250.png" width="200px"  alt=""/> CSE1110 Structured Programming 1 (JavaScript) </h2>
		<button class="collapsible">Expand - Program of Studies</button>
		<div class="content">
			<p>Students are introduced to a general programming environment in which they write simple structured algorithms and programs that input, process and output data, use some of the more basic operators and data types, and follow a sequential flow of control. <em>Prerequisite: None </em> </p>
		</div>
	</li>
	<li>
		<h2><img src="CSE1120 Google Classroom 1000-250.png" width="200px"  alt=""/> CSE1120 Structured Programming 2 (JavaScript) </h2>
		<button class="collapsible">Expand - Program of Studies</button>
		<div class="content">
			<p>Students work with structured programming constructs by adding the selection and iteration program control flow mechanisms to their programming repertoire. They write structured algorithms and programs that use blocks to introduce an element of modularity into their programming practice. <em>Prerequisite: CSE1110: Structured Programming 1  </em> </p>
		</div>
	</li>
</ul>
<hr>
	<h2>Computer Graphics (Laser Cutter and Cricut) </h2>
<ul>
	<li>
		<h2><img src="DES1030 Google Classroom 1000-250.png" width="200px"  alt=""/> DES1030 2-D Design 1 (Illustrator) </h2>
		<button class="collapsible">Expand - Program of Studies</button>
		<div class="content">
			<p>Students develop skills and techniques for 2-D design by using tools, materials and processes common to 2-D design to complete a variety of project activities. <em>Prerequisite: DES1020: The Design Process </em> </p>
		</div>
	</li>
	<li>
		<h2><img src="DES2035 Google Classroom 1000-250.png" width="200px"  alt=""/> DES2035 2-D Design 2 (Illustrator) </h2>
		<button class="collapsible">Expand - Program of Studies</button>
		<div class="content">
			<p>Students continue to develop skills and techniques for 2-D design by using tools, materials and processes common to 2-D design to complete a variety of project activities. <em>Prerequisite: DES1030: 2-D Design 1   </em> </p>
		</div>
	</li>
</ul>
<hr>
