<h2>Electronic Sensors (Starting Robotics) </h2>
<ul>
	<li>
		<h2><img src="ELT1010 Google Classroom 1000-250.png" width="200px"  alt=""/> ELT1010 Electro-Assembly 1 (Raspberry PI) </h2>
		<button class="collapsible">Expand - Program of Studies</button>
		<div class="content">
			<p>Students apply basic fabricating and servicing techniques to construct and test electronic and electromagnetic devices and cables. <em>Prerequisite: None </em> </p>
		</div>
	</li>
	<li>
		<h2><img src="ELT2010 Google Classroom 1000-250.png" width="200px"  alt=""/> ELT2010 Electro-Assembly 2 (Raspberry Pi) </h2>
		<button class="collapsible">Expand - Program of Studies</button>
		<div class="content">
			<p>Students apply electro-assembly technology to manufacture circuit boards. <em> Prerequisite: ELT1010: Electro-assembly 1 </em> </p>
		</div>
	</li>
</ul>
<hr>
<h2>Accounting </h2>
<ul>
	<li>
		<h2><img src="FIN1010 Accounting Google Classroom 1000-250.png" width="200px"  alt=""/> FIN1010: Personal Financial Information </h2>
		<button class="collapsible">Expand - Program of Studies</button>
		<div class="content">
			<p>Students explore concepts that affect the finances of an individual, including a code of conduct, the economic environment, acquiring and using financial resources and the effects of government legislation. <em>Prerequisite: None   </em> </p>
		</div>
	</li>
	<li>
		<h2><img src="FIN1015 Accounting Google Classroom 1000-250.png" width="200px"  alt=""/> FIN1015: Accounting Prep (Ch1,3) </h2>
		<button class="collapsible">Expand - Program of Studies</button>
		<div class="content">
			<p>Students are introduced to accounting and terminology unique to financial accounting. They become familiar with financial statements, generally accepted accounting principles and how to prepare for the process of starting up a business. <em>Prerequisite: None   </em> </p>
		</div>
	</li>
	<li>
		<h2><img src="FIN1020 Accounting Google Classroom 1000-250.png" width="200px"  alt=""/> FIN1020: Accounting Cycle 1 (Ch 4,5) </h2>
		<button class="collapsible">Expand - Program of Studies</button>
		<div class="content">
			<p>Students are introduced to the accounting cycle for a service business. They will analyze and record business transactions up to trial balance for the fiscal period of a business using terminology unique to financial accounting. <em>Prerequisite: FIN1015: Accounting Prep   </em> </p>
		</div>
	</li>
	<li>
		<h2><img src="FIN1030 Accounting Google Classroom 1000-250.png" width="200px"  alt=""/> FIN1030: Accounting Cycle 2 (Ch 6,7) </h2>
		<button class="collapsible">Expand - Program of Studies</button>
		<div class="content">
			<p>Students complete the accounting cycle for a service business, preparing financial statements and closing accounts. They also will explore other factors of a business, including budgets. <em>Prerequisite: FIN1020: Accounting Cycle 1   </em> </p>
		</div>
	</li>
	<li>
		<h2><img src="FIN2020 Accounting Google Classroom 1000-250.png" width="200px"  alt=""/> FIN2020: Retail Accounting 1 (Ch 8,9) </h2>
		<button class="collapsible">Expand - Program of Studies</button>
		<div class="content">
			<p>Students apply specialized accounting procedures associated with buying and selling goods in a retail system with a credit system and a partnership. <em>Prerequisite: FIN1030: Accounting Cycle 2   </em> </p>
		</div>
	</li>
	<li>
		<h2><img src="FIN2030 Accounting Google Classroom 1000-250.png" width="200px"  alt=""/> FIN2030: Retail Accounting 2 (Ch10, 11) </h2>
		<button class="collapsible">Expand - Program of Studies</button>
		<div class="content">
			<p>Students continue to apply specialized accounting procedures by preparing financial statements, analyzing adjusting and closing entries and completing the accounting cycle for a retail business. <em>Prerequisite: FIN2020: Retail Accounting 1   </em> </p>
		</div>
	</li>
	<li>
		<h2><img src="FIN3010 Accounting Google Classroom 1000-250.png" width="200px"  alt=""/> FIN3010: Advanced Accounting (Ch13, 14 </h2>
		<button class="collapsible">Expand - Program of Studies</button>
		<div class="content">
			<p>Students apply advanced accounting procedures, including capital assets and uncollectible accounts, used by a variety of businesses. Students also prepare adjustments, using the accrual method of accounting, and examine manufacturing or departmental accounting. <em>Prerequisite: FIN2030: Retail Accounting 2   </em> </p>
		</div>
	</li>
	<li>
		<h2><img src="FIN3020 Accounting Google Classroom 1000-250.png" width="200px"  alt=""/> FIN3020: Management Accounting (Ch 15, 16) </h2>
		<button class="collapsible">Expand - Program of Studies</button>
		<div class="content">
			<p>Students examine and explain management accounting, which involves optimizing capital assets for maximum return on investments. Students also examine various internal systems used to safeguard business assets. <em>Prerequisite: FIN2030: Retail Accounting 2   </em> </p>
		</div>
	</li>
	<li>
		<h2><img src="FIN3030 Accounting Google Classroom 1000-250.png" width="200px"  alt=""/> FIN3030: Capital Accounting (Ch 17, 18) </h2>
		<button class="collapsible">Expand - Program of Studies</button>
		<div class="content">
			<p>Students examine the accounting procedures related to proprietorships, partnerships, corporations and other entities. Students determine the effect the different forms of business ownership have on the equity section of the balance sheet. <em>Prerequisite: FIN2030: Retail Accounting 2   </em> </p>
		</div>
	</li>
	<li>
		<h2><img src="FIN3040 Accounting Google Classroom 1000-250.png" width="200px"  alt=""/> FIN3040: Financial Statements (Ch 19, 20) </h2>
		<button class="collapsible">Expand - Program of Studies</button>
		<div class="content">
			<p>Students examine the content and structure of financial statements and prepare customized financial statements for a variety of businesses. <em>Prerequisite: FIN2030: Retail Accounting 2   </em> </p>
		</div>
	</li>
	<li>
		<h2><img src="FIN3080 Accounting Google Classroom 1000-250.png" width="200px"  alt=""/> FIN3080: Personal Investment Planning 1 </h2>
		<button class="collapsible">Expand - Program of Studies</button>
		<div class="content">
			<p>Students are introduced to the capital market and the available securities when building a personal investment portfolio. Students research and analyze a variety of securities, including equities, fixed income and mutual funds. <em>Prerequisite: None   </em> </p>
		</div>
	</li>
</ul>
